## Assignment Strategies

### Manual Assignment

<Tabs>
  <Tab title="Direct Assignment">
    Assign specific conversations to team members:

    1. Open conversation
    2. Click **Assign** button
    3. Select team member from dropdown
    4. (Optional) Add assignment note
    5. Click **Assign**

    **When to use:**
    - Customer requests specific agent
    - Specialized expertise needed
    - Conversation continuation
    - VIP customers
  </Tab>

  <Tab title="Self-Assignment">
    Team members claim conversations:

    1. Browse unassigned conversations
    2. Click conversation to preview
    3. Click **Assign to Me**
    4. Start responding

    **When to use:**
    - Open queue system
    - Team has balanced skills
    - Flexible workload distribution
  </Tab>

  <Tab title="Reassignment">
    Transfer conversation to another agent:

    1. Open conversation
    2. Click current assignee name
    3. Select new team member
    4. Add handoff note:
       ```
       Customer needs help with [specific issue].
       Already tried: [attempted solutions]
       Next step: [recommended action]
       ```
    5. Confirm transfer

    **Best practice:** Always add context when reassigning.
  </Tab>
</Tabs>

### Automatic Assignment

Enable smart auto-assignment based on rules:

<AccordionGroup>
  <Accordion title="Round Robin">
    Distribute conversations evenly across team:

    **Configuration:**
    ```javascript
    {
      "strategy": "round_robin",
      "skip_offline": true,
      "max_concurrent": 10
    }
    ```

    **How it works:**
    1. New conversation arrives
    2. System checks next agent in rotation
    3. Assigns if agent is available
    4. Moves to next agent if unavailable
    5. Repeats cycle
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Load Balancing">
    Assign to agent with fewest active conversations:

    **Configuration:**
    ```javascript
    {
      "strategy": "load_based",
      "consider_priority": true,
      "max_per_agent": 15
    }
    ```

    **Factors considered:**
    - Current conversation count
    - Agent status (available, busy, away)
    - Conversation priority
    - Agent capacity limit
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Skill-Based">
    Route based on agent expertise:

    **Configuration:**
    ```javascript
    {
      "strategy": "skill_based",
      "skills": {
        "billing": ["alice@company.com", "bob@company.com"],
        "technical": ["charlie@company.com"],
        "sales": ["diana@company.com"]
      },
      "fallback": "round_robin"
    }
    ```

    **Setup:**
    1. Define skill categories
    2. Tag agents with skills
    3. Tag conversations with topics
    4. System matches automatically
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="VIP Routing">
    Prioritize high-value customers:

    **Configuration:**
    ```javascript
    {
      "strategy": "vip_routing",
      "vip_tags": ["premium", "enterprise"],
      "vip_agents": ["senior-agent@company.com"],
      "priority_boost": true
    }
    ```

    **How to mark VIP:**
    1. Add "VIP" tag to contact
    2. Set custom field: `customer_tier: "premium"`
    3. System routes to designated agents
  </Accordion>
</AccordionGroup>

